Algorithm : 
1. Start.
2. Initialize sum to 0.
3. Input the range limit n (the maximum number to check).
4. For each number i from 1 to n:
If i is even (i % 2 == 0), add i to sum.
5. Print the value of sum.
6. Stop.

Pseudocode : 
START
SET sum = 0
PRINT "Enter the range limit (n):"
INPUT n
FOR i = 1 TO n DO
    IF i MOD 2 == 0 THEN
        sum = sum + i
    ENDIF
END FOR
PRINT "The sum of even numbers is:", sum
STOP

Flowchart:
A[Start] --> B[Input n: Ask the user for the range limit]
    B --> C[Initialize sum = 0]
    C --> D[Set i = 1]
    D --> E{Is i <= n?}
    E --> F[Is i even?]
    F --> G[Add i to sum]:::yes
    F --> H[Skip]:::no
    G --> I[Increment i by 1]
    H --> I
    I --> E
    E --> J[Print sum]:::done
    J --> K[End]
